There's a total only `six` possible answers:
`1, 2, 3, 4, 7 and 8`
```
public int flipLights(int n, int m) {
            if (n == 1 && m > 0) {
                return 2;
            } else if (n == 2 && m == 1) {
                return 3;
            } else if ((n > 2 && m == 1) || (n == 2 && m > 1)) {
                return 4;
            } else if (n > 2 && m == 2) {
                return 7;
            } else if (n > 2 && m > 2) {
                return 8;
            } else {
                return 1;
            }
        }
```

One can imagine there's a 2d array `dp` with `m` rows and `n` columns, suppose m == 5 and n == 7, this `dp` matrix will be like the following:

```
2, 3, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 
2, 4, 7, 7, 7, 7, 7, 
2, 4, 8, 8, 8, 8, 8, 
2, 4, 8, 8, 8, 8, 8, 
2, 4, 8, 8, 8, 8, 8,
```

As `m` and `n` extend, the result will be fixed, so a total only 6 possible answers, we could basically "hardcode" them as the above.

Also viewable [here](https://github.com/fishercoder1534/Leetcode/blob/master/src/main/java/com/fishercoder/solutions/_672.java) on Github.

