solutions.content:
Great question indeed.

Here's the logic:

Let 0 = switched off, 1 = switched on.

* You don't have to simulate the entire process (e.g. press buttons 1000 times, for each time, randomly select button 1 to 4).

* Instead, notice the **base cases**: 

	1. If you press 1 button **even** number of times (e.g. 0, 2, 4, ...), **the effect cancelled out**. (on->off->on->off...->on->off). So, the initial state (all switched off) = "00...000" is possible.
	2. In contrast, If you press 1 button **odd** number of times, it is **equivalent to pressing 1 of the four buttons 1 time.**

* Next, you shall notice that you can press 2, 3 or 4 **distinct** buttons odd number of times to create **distinct** states. The exact figure of pressing button one to four is irrelevant.

	* For example, if you have a press sequence like "11233223321244", that's equivalent to pressing "12". 

* Also, Recall simple combination, 4C2 = 6, 4C3 = 4, 4C4 = 1.

* And notices that:

	1. If the **even number of counts >= 2**, then you can press two buttons odd number of times.
	a. For example, if number of counts = 4, you can press one button 3 times, and the second button 1 time.

Based on all those rules, you can derive the conditionals easily.

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    set<string> res;
    string opt1(string s) {
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) { s[i] = s[i] == '0' ? '1' : '0'; }
        return s;
    }
    string opt2(string s) {
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i+=2) { s[i] = s[i] == '0' ? '1' : '0'; }
        return s;
    }
    string opt3(string s) {
        for (int i = 1; i < s.length(); i+=2) { s[i] = s[i] == '0' ? '1' : '0'; }
        return s;
    }
    string opt4(string s) {
        int k;
        int len = s.length();
        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) { k = 3 * i; if (k >= len) { break; } s[k] = s[k] == '0' ? '1' : '0'; }
        return s;
    }
    int flipLights(int n, int p) {
        string init(n, '0');
        res.clear();
        if (p == 0)
            return 1;
        if ((p & 1) == 0) {
            res.insert(init);
        }
        if ((p & 1) != 0) {
            res.insert(opt1(init));
            res.insert(opt2(init));
            res.insert(opt3(init));
            res.insert(opt4(init));
        }
        if (p >= 2) {
            if ((p >= 2 && p % 2 == 0 && ((p / 2) & 1) != 0) || 
                (p >= 4 && ((p - 2) & 1) == 0) ||
                (p >= 6 && ((p - 4) & 1) == 0)) {
                res.insert(opt2(opt1(init)));
                res.insert(opt3(opt1(init)));
                res.insert(opt4(opt1(init)));
                res.insert(opt3(opt2(init)));
                res.insert(opt4(opt2(init)));
                res.insert(opt4(opt3(init)));
            }
        }
        if (p >= 3 && (p & 1) != 0) {
            res.insert(opt3(opt2(opt1(init))));
            res.insert(opt4(opt2(opt1(init))));
            res.insert(opt4(opt3(opt1(init))));
            res.insert(opt4(opt3(opt2(init))));            
        }
        if (p >= 4) {
            if ((p % 4 == 0 && ((p / 4) & 1) != 0) ||
                (((p - 3) & 1) != 0) ||
                (((p - 2) & 1) == 0) ||
                (((p - 1) & 1) != 0)) {
                res.insert(opt4(opt3(opt2(opt1(init)))));
            }
        }
        return res.size();
    }
};
```

