the idea is basicly the same with LIS prolem, create one extra hashtable, dp[k][x]  will help us store the number of LIS  (which has a length of k) ends with number x. So each time after we found the index to replace the current number x in table by binary search just increase the number of lcs which ends with current number and has a length of index + 1 equal to sum(dp[index-1][j]  for j in dp[index-1] if j < x).
```
class Solution:
    def findNumberOfLIS(self, nums):
        dp = collections.defaultdict(collections.Counter)
        dp[-1][-1e9] = 1
        table = []
        for i in nums:
            index = bisect.bisect_left(table, i)
            if index == len(table):
                table.append(i)
            else:
                table[index] = i 
            dp[index][i] += sum(dp[index-1][j] for j in dp[index-1] if j < i)
        return sum(dp[max(0, len(table)-1)].values()) 
