Runtime: 150 ms, faster than 92.49% of C++ online submissions for Number of Longest Increasing Subsequence.
# *Intuition:*

**Finding LIS:**
First of all we need to find the LIS of the given array. For that need to iterate from left to right.
Lets Take a number (suppose index i ). As we are trying to find Longest Strictly increasing Subsequence, we will try to place our number after every number from index 0 to i-1 which is less than our current number.Then we choose the index which gives us the longest chain of number and store that number in that particular index and the path in the Route vector.

**EXAMPLE:**

**nums = [1,3,5,4,7]**
**dp = [0,0,0,0,0]**
**Route vector:
0- >
1 ->
2 ->
3 ->
4 ->**

1. We take 1, as it is the first number we can't put it after any number. So, we put value = 1 in 0th index.
 **nums = [1,3,5,4,7]**
 **dp = [1,0,0,0,0]**
 **Route vector (Index -> Path):
0- >
1 ->
2 ->
3 ->
4 ->**

2. We take 3. As 3 is greater than 1, we can place it after 1. So, our value of **1st index = 0th index + 1 = 2** and we **push 0 in the 1st index** of the Route vector because this is our desired path to current LIS.
 **dp = [1,2,0,0,0]**
 **nums = [1,3,5,4,7]**
 **Route vector (Index -> Path):
0- >
1 -> 0
2 ->
3 ->
4 ->**

3. We take 5 and try to place after 3. As 3<5 we can place it and our value of **2nd index = 1st index + 1 = 3** and** push 1 in the 2nd index** of the Route vector. Now we try to place it before 1. As 1<5, we can place it their and our value will become **0th index + 1 = 2** . As we already have value = 3 in our current index, we will not take the new value.
**dp = [1,2,3,0,0]**
**nums = [1,3,5,4,7]**
**Route vector (Index -> Path):
0- >
1 ->0
2 ->1
3 ->
4 ->**

 4. We take 4 and try to place it after 5. As 5>4 we can't place it here. 
Then we take 3. As 3<4, we can place it here and the new value becomes **1st index + 1 = 2+1 = 3** and we **push 1 in the 3rd index** of the Route vector.
 Then we take 1. As 1 < 4 we can place it here and the new value will be = 1+1 = 2. As we already have value = 3, we won't take anything smaller than our current value.
**dp = [1,2,3,3,0]**
**nums = [1,3,5,4,7]**
**Route vector (Index -> Path):
0- >
1 ->0
2 ->1
3 ->1
4 ->**

5. We take 7 and try to place it after 4. As 4<7 we can place it here and the new value becomes **3rd index + 1 = 3+1 = 4** and we **push 3 in the 4th index** of the Route vector. 
Then we take 5 and as 5<7 we can place our number after it and the value becomes **2nd index + 1 = 3+1 = 4.** As our **curr value = new found value** so we won't be updating our answer but we will **push 2 in in the 4th index** of our Route vector. After that we take 3 , 1 one by one but none of them will give us greater or equal value compare to our current value.
**dp = [1,2,3,3,4]**
**nums = [1,3,5,4,7]**
**Route vector (Index -> Path):
0- >
1 ->0
2 ->1
3 ->1
4 -> 3 -> 2**


**DFS:**

Now from our dp array we know that, our LIS is 4. So will iterate through our dp array and if we find any LIS value = 4 , we can certain say that a **Longest strictly increasing subsequence ends here**. So, as we already created a graph using our **route vector**, we can start a dfs taking the **index value of dp as a root**.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/57f1d9c5-f734-40cd-bc53-bf752c71494c_1668220623.598379.png)

As running a dfs will be time consuming, we will be storing (**memoization**) the value of the subtree in a array named SAVE. Using this save array, we won't have to go through the same subtree again. The code will provide a better and clear view.

# CODE (C++):

```
class Solution {
public:

    vector<int>Route_vector[2002];

    int save[2003];
    int dfs(int x){
        if(Route_vector[x].size() == 0) // We cant go any further, so thats a complete path
            return 1;

        if(save[x]!=0) // We already went through this subPath earlier, so we saved it
            return save[x];

        for(int i=0;i<Route_vector[x].size();i++)
            save[x]+=dfs(Route_vector[x][i]); 
        return save[x];
    }


    int findNumberOfLIS(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        int dp[n];
        int ans = 0;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            dp[i] = 1;
            for(int j=i-1;j>=0;j--){
                if(nums[j]<nums[i]) // We found a number which is less than our choosen number
                {
                    if(dp[i] == dp[j]+1) // If our current dp[] value is equal to new value, we will just update our path
                        Route_vector[i].push_back(j);

                    else if(dp[j]+1>dp[i]){ // If our current dp[] value is less than new value, we erase our path and start a new path
                        dp[i] = dp[j]+1;
                        Route_vector[i].clear();
                        Route_vector[i].push_back(j);
                    }
                }    
            }
            ans = max(ans,dp[i]); // Keeping track of the maximum LIS length
        }
        int res = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
            if(dp[i] == ans) // we will run dfs and take iTH index as a root if dp[i] = longest LIS
                res+=dfs(i);
        return res;
    }
};
```

