# Intuition
The problem asks us to find the number of longest increasing subsequences in the given array. To solve this problem efficiently, we can use dynamic programming.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
The time complexity of this solution is O(n^2), where n is the size of the input array nums. The outer loop runs for n iterations, and the inner loop also runs for a maximum of n iterations.

- Space complexity:
The space complexity is O(n) since we are using two additional vectors, dp and cnt, both of size n, to store the lengths of subsequences and their counts.

# Code
