The idea is straightforward, we use a variable `max_length` to track longest continuous increasing subsequence ending at `nums[i]`(inclusive) . To update `max_length`, there has 2 sceanarios:
1. If `nums[i-1]` < `nums[i]`,  we use previous `max_length` at `i-1` and add 1 to it as current `max_length` at index `i`.
2. If `nums[i-1]` >= `nums[i]`, the `max_length` at index `i` is just itself, which means 1.
