solutions.content:
Define `dp[i]` to be the length of the longest increasing subarray (LIS) ending at `nums[i]`. Initially, `dp[i] = 1`. For each `i > 0`, if `nums[i] > nums[i - 1]`, update `dp[i] = dp[i - 1] + 1`. Return the maximum value of `dp`.

Since `dp[i]` only depends on `dp[i - 1]`, we can just use a single variable and update it. Another key point to make the codes clean is how to handle empty array.

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int findLengthOfLCIS(vector<int>& nums) {
        int ans = 0;
        for (int i = 0, l = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
            i && nums[i] > nums[i - 1] ? l++ : l = 1;
            ans = max(ans, l);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

