solutions.content:
I am using Coursera algorithms (Princeton, Robert Sedgewick) course ideas so code should be easy to understand if you watched it.
Idea is based on building a Graph from the matrix using adjucencyMap representation and then use BFS to fins path from shortest tree to next shortest tree in this graph:
Step 1a: build adjucency HashMap (graph) of cells we can visit
Step 1b: build TreeMap (treeHeight, index) in order to know which trees to visit first 
Step 2: run BFS to find distance from start to shortestTree; start = shortestTreeIndex after
Step 3: visit and cut trees in order from shortest one, if tree cannot be reached -> return -1

**Note: this solution is extremely slow (bottom 5% on speed and memory by leetcode mertics)**

It supposed to be:
```
M == forest.length
N == forest[i].length
O(MN) -> building adjucency Map
O(MN)*log(MN) -> building heightIndexMap (TreeMap)
O(MN * (MN + 4MN)) -> running BFS to find shortest pathts between shortest and nextShortest tree.
Time complexity of BFS is O(V + E) when Adjacency List is used.
For each tree we can have maximum of 4*MN edges and we are running BFS MN times, so it totales to O(MN * (MN + 4MN))
```
Tme complexity is sum of the above, which can be simplified to O(MN * (MN + 4MN)) = O((MN)^2)

**Bonus: the solution should work if input is not a matrix, but a `List<List<Integer>> forest` with random number of cells in each row**


```
class Solution {
    Map<Integer, List<Integer>> adjucencyMap;
    Map<Integer, Integer> heightIndexMap;
    int forestSize = 0;

    public int cutOffTree(List<List<Integer>> forest) {
        if(forest.get(0).get(0) == 0){
            //(0,0) point is blocked
            return -1;
        }

        adjucencyMap = new HashMap<>();        
        //we use TreeMap so that trees will be sorted by height
        heightIndexMap = new TreeMap<>();
        forestSize = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i<forest.size(); i++){
            for(int j = 0; j<forest.get(i).size(); j++){    
                int cell = forest.get(i).get(j);
                int index = i*forest.get(i).size() + j + 1;
                //only consider trees we need to cut, ignore "1's"
                if(cell > 1){
                    heightIndexMap.put(forest.get(i).get(j), index);
                }

                //only consider walkable cells
                if(cell > 0) {
                    List<Integer> adjucent = new ArrayList<>();
                    if(j-1 >= 0 && forest.get(i).get(j-1) > 0){
                        //add left
                        adjucent.add(index - 1);  
                    }
                    if(j+1 < forest.get(i).size() && forest.get(i).get(j+1) > 0){
                        //add right
                        adjucent.add(index + 1);  
                    }
                    if(i-1 >= 0 && j < forest.get(i-1).size() && forest.get(i-1).get(j) > 0){
                       //add top
                        adjucent.add(index - forest.get(i-1).size()); 

                    }
                    if(i+1 < forest.size() && j < forest.get(i+1).size() && forest.get(i+1).get(j) > 0){
                        //add bot
                        adjucent.add(index + forest.get(i).size()); 
                    }               
                    adjucencyMap.put(index, adjucent);                        
                }

                forestSize++;
            }
        }

        int result = 0;
        int startIndex = 1;
        List<Integer> sortedTrees = new ArrayList(heightIndexMap.keySet());

        for(int i = 0; i < sortedTrees.size(); i++){
            int height = sortedTrees.get(i);
            int targetIndex = heightIndexMap.get(height);
            int dist = bfsFindDist(startIndex, targetIndex);
            if(dist == -1){
                return dist;
            }
            result += dist;
            startIndex = targetIndex;
        }

       return result;
    }

    // return: distance from startTreeIndex to targetTreeIndex
    // -1 if no path found
    int bfsFindDist(int startTreeIndex, int targetTreeIndex){
        if(startTreeIndex == targetTreeIndex){
            return 0;
        }

        List<Integer> distances = new ArrayList<>();
        for(int i = 0; i<=forestSize; i++){
            distances.add(i, -1);
        }

        List<Boolean> visited = new ArrayList<>();
        for(int i = 0; i<=forestSize; i++){
            visited.add(i, false);
        }

        visited.set(startTreeIndex, true);
        distances.set(startTreeIndex, 0);      
        Queue<Integer> queue = new LinkedList<>();
        queue.add(startTreeIndex);
        while(!queue.isEmpty()){
            int tree = queue.remove();
            for(int adj : adjucencyMap.get(tree)){
                if(adj == targetTreeIndex){
                    return distances.get(tree)+1;
                }
                if(!visited.get(adj)){
                    queue.add(adj);
                    visited.set(adj, true);
                    distances.set(adj, distances.get(tree)+1);
                }
            }
        }

        return distances.get(targetTreeIndex);
    }
}
```

